    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe current markdown parser with treesitter for things like lsp info is amazing, but it always fails to add syntax highlighting if the language name is not full but shortcut. \r\n\r\ne.g. when you put the \\```js instead of \\```javascript you'll get something like this\r\n<img width=\"1148\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/16926049/8b0750df-c8af-4b47-97ef-3f9bd0498dd7\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nAdd the most popular shorthands for the languages like \r\n\r\n- ts -> typescript\r\n- tsx -> typescript react \r\n- js -> javascript\r\n- jsx -> javascript react\r\n\r\n\r\n### Version\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1793+g808fbe67a\r\nBuild type: RelWithDebInfo\r\nLuaJIT 2.1.1700008891",
    "closed_at": "2023-12-10T05:02:54Z",
